<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<p><a name="Explanatory_notes" id="Explanatory_notes"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Explanatory notes</span></h3>
<div class="references-small">
<p><b>a.</b> <cite id="endnote_Anone"><a href="#ref_Anone" title=""><b><sup>^</sup></b></a></cite>&#160; Times given are in ship time, the local time for <i>Titanic</i><span style="padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>s position in the Atlantic. On the night of the sinking, this was approximately one and half hours ahead of EST and two hours behind GMT.</p>
<p><b>b.</b> <cite id="endnote_Bnone"><a href="#ref_Bnone" title=""><b><sup>^</sup></b></a></cite>&#160; The Library of Congress and Leo Marriot's <i>Titanic</i> identify this as <i>Olympic</i>, Dr Robert Ballard's <i>Exploring the Titanic</i> and Daniel Allen Butler's <i>Unsinkable: The Full Story of the RMS Titanic</i> identify this as <i>Titanic</i>.</p>
</div>
